    "Cs are expressed in terms of billions of operations and provides a way of quantifying the computational resources required by a machine learning model.",
    "The results of the latency and GMACs of the models, as well as the model sizes, are presented in Table 6.",
    "These measurements were conducted using a V100 32G GPU.",
    "The results show that there is a trade-off between accuracy and efficiency of the models.",
    "The ClinicalBioBERT model, which is listed only as representative of a class of larger-sized models (110m parameters, as listed in Table 4), has the best performance on the test sets but has the highest latency and GMACs, making it less suitable for deployment in resource-constrained environments."
